The paper deals with Social Choice theory, which is a subfield of Game Theory (cs.GT). It also discusses the possibility of using AI to implement new Reality-aware voting rules (cs.AI). The paper proposes new models and concepts, which could fall under the sub-categories of Social Informatics (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its findings for democracy, which could fall under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it deals with decision-making processes.
